#: ../../B/black-art.rst:5
msgid "black art"
msgstr "black art"

#: ../../B/black-art.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/black-art.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] A collection of arcane, unpublished, and (by implication) mostly "
"ad-hoc techniques developed for a particular application or systems area "
"(compare :ref:`black-magic`\\). VLSI design and compiler code optimization "
"were (in their beginnings) considered classic examples of black art; as "
"theory developed they became :ref:`deep-magic`\\, and once standard "
"textbooks had been written, became merely :ref:`heavy-wizardry`\\. The huge "
"proliferation of formal and informal channels for spreading around new "
"computer-related technologies during the last twenty years has made both the"
" term black art and what it describes less common than formerly. See also "
":ref:`voodoo-programming`\\."
msgstr ""
"特定のアプリケーションやシステム領域のために開発された、難解で未発表の、(言外に)たいていその場しのぎの技法の集まり(\\ :ref:`black-"
"magic`\\ と比較せよ)。VLSI設計やコンパイラのコード最適化は、(その始まりにおいては)black "
"artの典型例とみなされた。理論が発展するとそれらは\\ :ref:`deep-magic`\\ となり、標準的な教科書が書かれると、単なる\\ "
":ref:`heavy-wizardry`\\ "
"になった。この20年間にコンピューター関連の新技術を広めるための公式・非公式の経路が膨大に増えたことで、black "
"artという用語も、それが表すものも、以前より一般的でなくなった。\\ :ref:`voodoo-programming`\\ も参照。"
